
# Sage Legal Aid

Sage Legal Aid is an AI-powered legal information assistant designed to help users understand legal topics, navigate legal processes, and receive guidance in plain, understandable language.  
This tool leverages Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Large Language Models (LLMs) to make legal knowledge more accessible.

---

## 🚀 Features

- **AI Legal Assistant** – Ask legal questions and get AI-powered answers.
- **Natural Language Understanding** – Understands everyday language queries.
- **Document Assistance** – Summarize and explain legal text.
- **Search & Retrieval** – Retrieves legal references for better accuracy.
- **User-Friendly Interface** – Simple, intuitive UI for easy interaction.

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```

sage-legal-aid-main/
│
├── backend/              # Server-side logic, APIs, and AI integration
├── frontend/             # Web-based user interface
├── data/                 # Legal datasets or reference material
├── requirements.txt      # Python dependencies
├── package.json          # Frontend dependencies (if using React/Vue)
├── README.md             # Project documentation
└── ...

````

---

## 🛠️ Installation

### Prerequisites
- Python **3.9+**
- Node.js **16+** (if using frontend build)
- pip (Python package manager)
- npm or yarn (Frontend package manager)

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/sage-legal-aid.git
cd sage-legal-aid
````

### 2️⃣ Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3️⃣ Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

---

## ▶️ Usage

### Start Backend Server

```bash
cd backend
python app.py
```

(Default runs on `http://localhost:5000`)

### Start Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm start
```

(Usually runs on `http://localhost:3000`)

---

## ⚙️ Configuration

Set up environment variables in `.env` file for API keys, database configs, and other secrets:

```
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key
DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
```

